cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with distributed optimization algorithms and their running times. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the diameter of disjoint connected parts of a network and proposes a solution to circumvent the problem. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel construction algorithm for finding low congestion shortcuts. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper discusses planar networks and bounded genus graphs. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with optimization problems and their lower bounds.
